Q1. A "good string" is a string that starts with the letter 'a' & has a length >3. Write a Program to find if a string is good or not.

Q2. Predict the output of following code :
let num = 12;
if ((num%3 === 0) && ( (num+1 ==15) || (num-1 == 11) ) ) {
   console.log("safe");
} else {
   console.log("unsafe");
}
